[The case count is climbing with the most recent tally at 571 cases including 17 deaths in 25 provinces. In the past 24 hours, 24 provinces (including autonomous regions and municipalities) have reported 131 new confirmed cases and 8 new deaths. All deaths to date have occurred in Wuhan City. Per the clinical histories given above, 14 of the 17 reported deaths occurred individuals older than 65 years of age (average age 73.3 years), most with known pre-existing co-morbidities. Cases to date have been reported to have a history of contact in Wuhan, but there may be a bias as it is part of the case definition.

